'''Vestby Station''' ({{lang-no|Vestby stasjon}}) is a [[Train station|railway station]] located at the village of [[Vestby]], [[Norway]] on the railway [[<U+00D8>stfold Line|<U+00D8>stfoldbanen]]. The station is served by commuter trains between [[Spikkestad]] via [[Oslo]] to [[Moss]] with half hour or hourly headway by [[Norwegian State Railways|Norges Statsbaner]]. The station opened in 1879, and has about 160 passengers to Oslo each day.<ref name=njk>{{cite web |url=http://forsk.njk.no/stdb/index.php?mod=st&aut=&detaljert=1&baneID=220&Stnr=1312&sid=417 |title=Vestby |work=[[Norwegian Railway Club]] |accessdate=27 August 2010 |language=Norwegian}}</ref>

==History==
[[File:73sett sydVestby 04.jpg|thumb|left|alt=A four-car multiple unit running along a double-track line between two cliffs; in the background is a motorway.|[[NSB Class 73|Class 73b]] train on the double-track section of the [[<U+00D8>stfold Line]] near Vestby]]
The station was opened in 1879 as part of <U+00D8>stfoldbanen.<ref>[http://www.romeiendom.no/vaare-eiendommer/vestby-stasjon Vestby stasjon], ''[[Rom Eiendom]]''. Retrieved 27 August 2010 {{language icon|no}}</ref> When the stretch between [[Ski Station]] and Moss was extended to [[double track]] in 1990s, Vestby Station received a major renovation.<ref name=jernbaneverket>[http://web.archive.org/web/20071219133909/http://www.jernbaneverket.no/jernbanenettet/stasjonssok/stasjonsoversikt/article.jhtml?articleID=1590288 Vestby Station], ''[[Norwegian National Rail Administration]]''. Retrieved 27 August 2010 {{language icon|no}}</ref><ref>[http://www.regjeringen.no/nb/dep/md/tema/planlegging_plan-_og_bygningsloven/kommuneplanlegging/innsigelsessaker/2010/Vestby-kommune-innsigelse-til-reguleringsplan-for-Sole-skog-skole-og-idrettsanlegg.html?id=602093 Vestby kommune, innsigelse til reguleringsplan for Sole skog skole og idrettsanlegg], ''[[Norwegian Ministry of the Environment]]''. Retrieved 27 August 2010 {{language icon|no}}</ref> A regulation plan for the station area was released May 2010, which aimed at increasing the station's parking places.<ref name=parkering>{{cite web|title=Vedtatt reguleringsplan for Vestby stasjon, innfartsparkering|url=http://www.vestby.kommune.no/vedtatt-reguleringsplan-for-vestby-stasjon-innfartsparkering.4785164-81880.html|work=[[Vestby|Municipality of Vestby]]|accessdate=27 August 2010|author=Plansjefen|language=Norwegian}}</ref> In June 2010, the station building caught fire at the middle of the night, but left no injuries.<ref name=fire>{{cite news|last=Rypeng|first=Lisa|title=Brann p<U+00E5> Vestby stasjon|url=http://www.oblad.no/nyheter/brann-pa-vestby-stasjon-1.5343710|accessdate=27 August 2010|work=<U+00D8>stlandets Blad|date=02 June 2010|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref name="fire2">{{cite web|last=Rom|first=Marianne W.|title=Brann p<U+00E5> Vestby stasjon|url=http://www.vestbyavis.no/nyheter/article5143410.ece|work=Vestby Avis|accessdate=27 August 2010|language=Norwegian|date=3 June 2010}}</ref> The station has also been victim of sabotage, when some local youth laid steel pipes over the tracks.<ref name="sabotage">{{cite web|title=Togsabotasje ved Vestby stasjon |url=http://pub.tv2.no/nettavisen/innenriks/article203672.ece|work=[[Nettavisen]]|accessdate=27 August 2010|language=Norwegian|date=22 March 2004}}</ref>

==Facilities==
The station did, as mentioned earlier, get a major overhaul as the Follo Line was extended to double track in the 1990s. The station is therefore designed in the same style as the new [[Sonsveien Station|station Sonsveien]], with a modern walkway over the tracks.<ref name=linjeark>[http://www.linjeark.no/broer.html Broer <U+00C5>s og Vestby], ''Linje arkitekter''. Bes<U+00F8>kt 27 August 2010 {{language icon|no}}</ref> The walkway is built in gluelam, and is integrated with the stations platforms into one minimalistic construction.<ref name=linjeark/> On the east side is a bus stop, on the west side is a park and ride facility with place for up to 120 cars.<ref name=parkering /> There is also a taxi stand at the station.<ref name=parkering />

The station has a station building, which is opened from 05.45-12.00 on workdays, and stores a small kiosk.<ref name=jernbaneverket /> The platforms have sheds and ticket machines. It is located north of Sonsveien Station and south of [[<U+00C5>s Station]] on the Follo Line, 38,65 kilometres from Oslo Central Station.<ref name=jernbaneverket /> 

==Service==
Vestby Station is served by the line 550 towards [[Moss Station|Moss]] of the [[Oslo Commuter Rail]], which is operated by the [[Norwegian State Railways]].<ref>[http://www.nsb.no/network-map/nsb-network-map-article29400-3599.html NSB network map], ''[[Norwegian State Railways]]''. Retrieved 27 August 2010</ref> The line runs between [[Spikkestad Station|Spikkestad]] and [[Moss Station|Moss]], through [[Oslo]] on the [[Spikkestad Line]] and [[Follo Line]], respectively.<ref>[http://www.nsb.no/getfile.php/www.nsb.no/nsb.no/Bilder/Rutetabeller/NSB%20Map.pdf NSB network map - NSB], ''[[Norwegian State Railways]]''. Retrieved 27 August 2010</ref> The service has two southbound stations before reaching Moss; [[Sonsveien Station|Sonsveien]] and [[Kambo Station|Kambo]].<ref>[http://www.nsb.no/getfile.php/www.nsb.no/nsb.no/Bilder/Rutetabeller/Lokaltogkart%20A4.pdf NSB Network Map commuter trains], ''[[Norwegian State Railways]]''. Retrieved 27 August 2010</ref> Travel time to [[Oslo Central Station]] is 33 minutes and to Moss 16 minutes.<ref>[http://www.nsb.no/rutetabeller/resultat/?timetablesearch-departure_station=VESTBY&timetablesearch-arrival_station=MOSS&timetablesearch-view_all_day=true&timetablesearch-friday=friday Rutetider Vestby - Moss], ''[[Norwegian State Railways]]''. Retrieved 27 August 2010 {{language icon|no}}</ref><ref>[http://www.nsb.no/rutetabeller/resultat/?timetablesearch-departure_station=OSLO+S&timetablesearch-arrival_station=VESTBY&timetablesearch-view_all_day=true&timetablesearch-friday=friday Rutetider Oslo S - Vestby], ''[[Norwegian State Railways]]''. Retrieved 27 August 2010 {{language icon|no}}</ref> The public transport authority Ruter operates bus services to the station from the conurbations around Vestby.<ref>[http://www.ostfold-kollektiv.no/userfiles/931.pdf 931 Moss - Kambo - Son - H<U+00F8>len - Vestby], Timetable. Retrieved 27 August 2010 {{language icon|no}}</ref>

